President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. These include Pamela J. H. Slutz as Ambassador to the Republic of Burundi, Gordon Gray as Ambassador to the Republic of Tunisia, Richard J. Schmierer as Ambassador to the Sultanate of Oman, Martha L. Campbell as Ambassador to the Republic of the Marshall Islands, Alfonso E. Lenhardt as Ambassador to the United Republic of Tanzania, Mark Gitenstein as Ambassador to Romania, Howard W. Gutman as Ambassador to Belgium, Don Beyer as Ambassador to Switzerland and the Principality of Lichtenstein, Vinai Thummalapally as Ambassador to Belize, and John Nay as Ambassador to the Republic of Suriname. President Obama expressed his confidence in these individuals and their ability to strengthen America's partnerships around the world.